The first line needs to be the array declaration. You cannot iterate over an array that does not exist. There are three possible choices for the loop. C uses the `;` to separate the three parts of a for loop, so the answer with a `,` is incorrect. When using for loops, declare the iterator variable first, then create the test condition, and finally increment the iterator variable. Don't forget to add the `}` to terminate the loop.

```python
char *animals[] = {"cat", "dog", "fish", "rabbit"};
for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
  printf("%s\n", animals[i]);
}
```

